HEADWORD: Trull
<hw>Trull</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. <ets>trolle</ets>,
<ets>trulle</ets>; cf. OD. <ets>drol</ets> a jester, Dan.
<ets>trold</ets> an elf, imp, Sw. <ets>troll</ets> a goblin, Icel.
<ets>troll</ets>, <ets>tr⟦oum⟧ll</ets>, a giant, fiend, demon. Cf.
<er>Droll</er>, <er>Troll</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A drab; a
strumpet; a harlot; a trollop.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A girl; a wench; a lass.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

